This paper deals with improving the performance of temporal-difference learning algorithms, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses state-dependent discounting and bootstrapping functions, which are relevant to reinforcement learning and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also touches on control systems, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and discusses data structures, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
